Context: Then he is very sure. 
Statement: He is very sure of himself. 
Answer: [/INST] 1. The "he" in the context and statement refer to the same person.
2. The speaker has conveyed through "then" that some previous statement or situation has led to his certainty.
3. The certainty mentioned in the context applies to his self-assurance, as indicated in the statement.</s>